                <span class="">Abraham Kimmelmann</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="kimmelmannA" start="9423.217" end="x">Was anybody asked if he was guilty? Did one have the right to defend himself? We wouldn't dare to say a word; he would get it right away double. In the beginning we tried—we didn't know it yet, so we tried to defend ourselves, so we would get still more.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="9438.792" end="x">That was at night?</span>
